<body>
    <h1>2026-03-16 SRE agent customer InfoSec questions</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <ul local-id=3D"69b96038-6561-46f4-aaa0-974ddf859f87">
<li local-id=3D"e1729024-01c0-45c5-811e-b6e67adccedc">
<p local-id=3D"bf8fa4d212bc">How does NR ingest data from other data source=
s.&nbsp; Define available sources and scopes.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f94025efbffa">
<li local-id=3D"3558dc17513f">
<p local-id=3D"462397ba5dfc">The agent queries data already in the customer=
's New Relic account =E2=80=94 metrics, logs, traces, events, alerts, and e=
ntity metadata =E2=80=94 via NerdGraph (GraphQL API) and internal MCP (Mode=
l Context Protocol) tool servers</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b95228c1bdf">
<p local-id=3D"53e4e43871e1"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"1e279511-4990-420a-a0d1-8e718c78f12b">What AI models are used and where=
 are they hosted</span></p>
<ul local-id=3D"16538a016c7b">
<li local-id=3D"cfebe2489d05">
<p local-id=3D"c74468050a64">This is subject to change without notice, but =
currently the SRE agent uses GPT 5.1 for general purpose and GPT 4o for con=
text summarization</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"8e1fbdea547b">
<p local-id=3D"35a3263e0fac">where is the data stored and how is it segment=
ed from other data</p>
<ul local-id=3D"64b240a4440e">
<li local-id=3D"c662924b615e">
<p local-id=3D"25d609c290bc">Stays in the customer's existing NR <span clas=
s=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b2bcfa18-0cb3-45a7-b368-d80d6910589=
b">data region (US or EU)</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"f5df160b-4d0a-445d-b4a7-8516df91bef4">
<p local-id=3D"6996d719c357">How is data stored and transmitted?&nbsp; Encr=
yption?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a6655b7b3e49">
<li local-id=3D"d0ac9ba0d8f8">
<p local-id=3D"699377e6091e">Aligned with our public documentation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"44dc4f3148e6">
<li local-id=3D"c332c1a760bb">
<p local-id=3D"56617db5d9b3"><a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearanc=
e=3D"inline" href=3D"https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/security/security-priva=
cy/data-privacy/security-controls-privacy/" local-id=3D"ee07555facaf" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/security/security-privacy/data=
-privacy/security-controls-privacy/</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f4a1d726bfbb">
<p local-id=3D"9e7697780b0a"><a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearanc=
e=3D"inline" href=3D"https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/security/security-priva=
cy/compliance/data-encryption/" local-id=3D"2fdb511a9557" rel=3D"nofollow">=
https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/security/security-privacy/compliance/data-en=
cryption/</a></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"afcf8d46-12b9-4304-b3d4-2fa364bd2479">
<p local-id=3D"d54b63ab754d">How does NR monitor model behavior?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"726935aaec3a">
<li local-id=3D"22afdb5f8b3d">
<p local-id=3D"47929869c3f9">NR instruments LLM calls via its own <a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/ai-monitoring/int=
ro-to-ai-monitoring" rel=3D"nofollow">AI Monitoring product</a> =E2=80=94 t=
racking latency, token usage, error rates, and model responses.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"ed15df0d-6c00-4fcc-8062-0b520676a17e">
<p local-id=3D"b5a7c0885b38">What 3rd party software/tools are used?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"1eae25609daa">
<li local-id=3D"a2b34eec8715">
<p local-id=3D"35739f358321">N/A</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"e3221f2e-849d-4346-8644-3b444b4e4f52">
<p local-id=3D"0fad541e0b9d">Are we able to filter personal information fro=
m ingestion?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"29a3c24e8735">
<li local-id=3D"1cb2df1948e3">
<p local-id=3D"f105449609d5">The SRE Agent operates on telemetry data alrea=
dy present in the customer's New Relic account. Customers control what data=
 is ingested using NR's data management tools (drop rules, obfuscation, log=
 parsing pipelines). The agent does not introduce new ingestion paths.</p><=
/li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"8ab72f8ad206">
<p local-id=3D"683bb4a997c3">What is your data deletion process?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"9d3f2fa26f64">
<li local-id=3D"b740334bd1d1">
<p local-id=3D"b60aa7ccdcab">Subject to standard <span class=3D"inline-comm=
ent-marker" data-ref=3D"d7291b4a-e7a5-48e9-8714-01a98d632a99">NR data reten=
tion policies </span>(customer-configurable). The agent doesn't create sepa=
rate copies.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"d02becb2-67cf-42d2-99e0-586984c862dd">
<p local-id=3D"aa3889ad9ab0">Do you log inputs and outputs?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"1b32a325f5eb">
<li local-id=3D"91559a743f95">
<p local-id=3D"5adafc0706ee">Yes =E2=80=94 the SRE Agent is instrumented wi=
th <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/ai-mon=
itoring/intro-to-ai-monitoring" rel=3D"nofollow">AI Monitoring (AIM)</a>, N=
R's observability product for LLM-powered applications. AIM captures sample=
d LLM request/response data as events in NRDB.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"c4e01799-e186-45e6-b2c9-157934ce2445">
<p local-id=3D"448d51d44bfd">Do we have the ability to limit scopes and fun=
ctionality of the agent?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"14cbc97d5b56">
<li local-id=3D"08a13ada3544">
<p local-id=3D"47277b0732b2">The agent's access is controlled by the System=
 Identity's role grants. Customers can limit which accounts, capabilities, =
and resources the agent can access</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"19d2b78f-1758-40d6-92bc-39f663c41532">
<p local-id=3D"e0809a8fc613">What types of controls do we have to manage us=
age/cost?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"eb1023743457">
<li local-id=3D"fed4a994dd3a">
<p local-id=3D"3a1683fb050d"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://doc=
s.newrelic.com/docs/accounts/accounts-billing/new-relic-one-pricing-billing=
/compute-budgets/overview" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Compute Budgets</strong=
></a> - NR's built-in cost management feature can help with monitoring the =
usage/cost of the <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"c0aa9c3=
d-9c8d-458d-ad40-3bcb1140184d">SRE agent feature</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"28fb4ee6-1d90-471c-b865-8bb51c7bfded">
<p local-id=3D"e69feacb1e31">What controls are in place to ensure agents do=
 not store, leak or misuse sensitive user data?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e2c08187e565">
<li local-id=3D"f005ef703335">
<p local-id=3D"e8377e1ea466">Each agent operates within a single customer's=
 organization boundary via System Identity auth</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f299211db8ae">
<p local-id=3D"4a5e6643a160">The agent can read customer data and query a c=
urated list of New Relic APIs, but has no capability to send data to extern=
al endpoints</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"71c2cb9d-c351-4f02-ad47-a6018718edd8">
<p local-id=3D"6fea25732c20">Will AI SRE use MCP servers?</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8785dfd66f6a">
<li local-id=3D"d65e3a77a65d">
<p local-id=3D"ef2e51a195e0">Yes. MCP (Model Context Protocol) is central t=
o the architecture.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
